  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are actively selling into this rally as SPX approaches the massive +78.8B gamma wall at 6580, with spot just 9 points below at 6571 - the 43.7% GEX surge indicates heavy call buying that's forcing dealers short and creating significant selling pressure above current levels. In this PIN regime, expect strong mean reversion with the 6580 strike acting as a magnet and ceiling, while any dip toward 6550 should see aggressive dealer buying given the -21.7B negative gamma pocket. Watch 6577 flip level closely - staying below keeps dealers in stabilizing mode, but a break above into negative gamma territory above 6580 could trigger momentum acceleration if the wall gets breached.",
